      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V lot used for screw manufacture (N=18 tensile coupons). Elastic modulus mean 114 GPa (CV 7%) and yield strength mean 880 MPa (CV 6.3%) exhibit wider scatter than typical for aerospace-grade Ti-6Al-4V, attributed to batch variability in the medical-device supply chain. This explicitly-low confidence in material inputs is fully documented; sensitivity analysis confirms these inputs drive the wide uncertainty bounds on all three QoIs. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws (N=5); dimensional tolerance within 0.02 mm.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
