      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition (5 mm/min, ambient temperature). Required level 3 demands at least two distinct test conditions (e.g. varied load rate or temperature) to assess condition sensitivity. Only one condition was tested due to resource constraints. This shortfall is accepted via the offset rationale below, supported by literature evidence that F1717 stiffness and yield force are insensitive to crosshead speed in the 1-10 mm/min range.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
